chassis.name: chassis

revisions.description: Added support for the controller cards and line cards.
Initial version of this MIB module.

chassis.description: Support for accessing trap notifications on chassis based products.

chassisCardRoleChangeNotify.name: chassisCardRoleChangeNotify
chassisCardRoleChangeNotify.description: A notification generated when the CFC's role is changed.

chassisCardJoinNotify.name: chassisCardJoinNotify
chassisCardJoinNotify.description: A notification generated when a card connects to the CFC.

chassisCardLeaveNotify.name: chassisCardLeaveNotify
chassisCardLeaveNotify.description: A notification generated when a card detaches from the CFC.

slotNumber.name: slotNumber
slotNumber.description: Slot number of the card that has changed.

chassisCardTable.name: chassisCardTable
chassisCardTable.description: A list of cards presented on the device.

chassisCardEntry.name: chassisCardEntry
chassisCardEntry.description: A table entry containing information about a card.

chassisCardSlot.name: chassisCardSlot
chassisCardSlot.description: The slot number the card is in.

chassisCardBoardOID.name: chassisCardBoardOID
chassisCardBoardOID.description: The OID value used to identify the type of board that is defined in the alliedTelesis's 'boards' enterprise MIB. If the board is provisioned or an unsupported hardware, this object will have the value of 0 0.

chassisCardName.name: chassisCardName
chassisCardName.description: The name of the card. E.g. AT-SBx81CFC400, AT-SBx81CFC960 for controller cards; AT-SBx81GP24, AT-SBx81GT24, AT-SBx81GS24, AT-SBx81XS6 for line cards; 'unknown' for unsupported hardware.

chassisCardState.name: chassisCardState
chassisCardState.description: The current state of the card. The valid state is in one of the following: unknown(1), configuring(2), syncing(3), online(4), syncingFirmware(5), joining(6), incompatibleSW(7), disabled(8), initializing(9), booting(10), unsupportedHW(11) or provisioned(12).

chassisCardControllerState.name: chassisCardControllerState
chassisCardControllerState.description: The current state of the controller card, in addition to the card state. The valid state is in one of the following: unknown(1), active(2) or standby(3).
